<item>
            <title>[HIVE-27995] Fix inconsistent behavior of LOAD DATA command for partitioned and non-partitioned tables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-27995</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For partitioned tables, while executing LOAD DATA/ LOAD DATA LOCAL commands, the check for file existence is not executed on HiveServer2, and this in turn throws an error during Runtime once the job is launched.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
java.io.FileNotFoundException: File file:/&amp;lt;filepath&amp;gt; does not exist.&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Non-partitioned tables do not follow this control flow, and the checks are run appropriately at compile time.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Incase the file does not exist, user is presented with the error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Invalid path &quot;file:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;///&amp;lt;filepath&amp;gt;: No files matching path file:/&amp;lt;filepath&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is inconsistent and error prone behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
